  "design_implications": [
    "Use exact Composite FIGI as the v1 U.S. tradable asset anchor; Share-class FIGI is a parent layer and one share class may legitimately map to multiple Composite-FIGI assets.",
    "Never generate or merge asset_id from CIK, ticker, name, ticker root, or Share-class FIGI alone.",
    "Allow accepted S5 ticker_change_event rows to attach only to an asset independently anchored by accepted S4 selected membership or accepted S6 Overview; unattached S5 event identities remain upstream review evidence and create no S7 identity.",
    "Use S4 daily active membership as the only interval spine; S6 first/last dates are observation envelopes and S5 events only corroborate boundaries.",
    "Associate an accepted S5 event to a ticker_alias interval only by exact Composite FIGI, exact case-sensitive ticker, ordinary_calendar_date quality, inclusive observed-date containment, and exactly one interval match; all other events remain unassociated review evidence.",
    "Keep unresolved active S4 rows visible and backtest-ineligible; do not silently drop them during identity enrichment.",
    "Emit no superseded asset or issuer state in v1 because the fixed six-release bundle contains no independently approved supersession source or availability rule.",
    "Treat 2026-captured names, SIC, type descriptions, and Overview fields as retrospective reference metadata rather than historical factor inputs."
  ],
